  "prompt": "What are some good engineering colleges in Pune?",
  "response": "Pune is home to several reputed engineering colleges. Here are some of the top engineering institutions in Pune:\n\n1. **College of Engineering Pune (COEP)**\n   - One of the oldest engineering colleges in India, COEP is highly respected for its academic excellence and research output.\n\n2. **Vishwakarma Institute of Technology (VIT)**\n   - Known for its strong industry connections and a wide array of engineering programs.\n\n3. **MIT World Peace University (MIT-WPU)**\n   - Offers a comprehensive engineering curriculum with a focus on holistic education.\n\n4. **Pune Institute of Computer Technology (PICT)**\n   - Specializes in computer science and IT-related courses and is known for its strong placement record.\n\n5. **Bharati Vidyapeeth Deemed University College of Engineering**\n   - Offers a variety of engineering courses and has good infrastructure and facilities.\n\n6. **Sinhgad College of Engineering**\n   - Known for its large campus and diverse engineering programs, with strong ties to the industry.\n\n7. **Dr. D. Y. Patil Institute of Technology**\n   - Offers a range of undergraduate and postgraduate engineering courses and emphasizes research and development.\n\n8. **Army Institute of Technology (AIT)**\n   - Exclusively for the children of army personnel, offering quality education and good placement opportunities.\n\n9. **Symbiosis Institute of Technology**\n   - Part of the Symbiosis International University, offering a modern curriculum and an industry-oriented approach.\n\n10. **Cummins College of Engineering for Women**\n    - Known for empowering women in the field of engineering with quality education and robust placement support.\n\nEach of these colleges has its own strengths, specializations, and unique offerings, so it's a good idea to research them further to find the best fit for your interests and career goals.",
